The
.i arguments
are passed to the map for arbitrary use.
Most map classes can interpolate these arguments
into their values using the syntax
d4305 1
a4305 1
to indicate the corresponding
d4307 2
a4308 3
Argument
.q %0
indicates the database key.
d4312 1
a4312 1
R$\- ! $+	$: $(uucp $1 $@@ $2 $: %1 @@ %0 . UUCP $)
a4322 3
