d5468 1
a5468 1
.ip "MAXLINE [2048]"
d5499 1
a5499 1
.ip "MAXRWSETS [200]"
a5501 6
The first half of these are reserved for numeric specification
(e.g., ``S92''),
while the upper half are reserved for auto-numbering
(e.g., ``Sfoo'').
Thus, with a value of 200 an attempt to use ``S99'' will succeed,
but ``S100'' will fail.
